Corne Vial workflow (code-first)

1) Bootstrap tools and local vial-qmk checkout
   kbd-setup

2) Build UF2 for your RP2040 ProMicro Corne rev1
   kbd-build-all

3) Flash
   - Enter bootloader (double-tap reset)
   - Copy the generated .uf2 onto RPI-RP2

4) Update with GUI changes from Vial
   - In Vial, export layout as .vil
   - Save it somewhere (for example ~/Downloads/corne.vil)
   - Import snapshot into your chezmoi-managed config:
     kbd-snapshot-add ~/Downloads/corne.vil
   - Commit in chezmoi repo:
     cd ~/.local/share/chezmoi && jj status && jj describe -m "add corne vial snapshot"

5) Keep source keymap authoritative
   - Main source: ~/.config/keyboard/corne-vial/keymaps/ezra_corne/
   - Snapshots: ~/.config/keyboard/corne-vial/snapshots/
